# 💸 Day 9 - Blind Auction

This is a simple console-based blind auction program written in Python for Day 9 of the **100 Days of Code** challenge.

Multiple users can enter their bids, which are kept secret until the end. The program then determines and announces the highest bidder.

## 🚀 Features

- Accepts multiple participants
- Keeps bids private until all are submitted
- Automatically identifies the highest bidder
- Option to restart the auction

## 🛠️ Built With

- Python 3

## 🧠 What I Practiced

- Dictionaries and data storage
- Loops and conditional logic
- Creating and calling functions
- Clearing the screen for better UX

---

Part of the [100 Days of Code](https://github.com/Synel96/100-Days-Of-Code) journey.
